al-verdict|archivedate=September 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=RAdalian>{{cite web|last=Adalian|first=Rouben Paul|authorlink=Rouben Paul Adalian|title=Armenian Genocide|location=Washington, DC |publisher= [[Armenian National Institute]]|url=http://www.armenian-genocide.org/genocide.html|date=2004|accessdate=August 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=de Zayas>{{cite web|last=de Zayas|first=Alfred|authorlink=Alfred de Zayas|title=The Genocide of the Armenians and the Relevance of the 1948 Genocide Convention|location=Beirut, Lebanon |publisher= [[Haigazian University Press]]}}</ref> -->\n\n\n<ref name=LookLex>{{cite web| url = http://lexicorient.com/e.o/assyrian_gc.htm  | title = Assyrian Genocide | work =Lexicorient}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=RwandaNews>{{cite news | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-13431486  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130509201153/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-13431486  | url-status = dead  | archive-date = 2013-05-09  | title = Rwanda: How the genocide happened  | work =  [[BBC]] | date =  2004-04-01 | quote = gives an estimate of 800,000}} and {{cite web| url = https://www.un.org/en/africarenewal/subjindx/121rwan.htm   | title =OAU sets inquiry into Rwanda genocide  | work =Africa Recovery  | volume= 12 | issue = 1#1   | date =August 1998 | page = 4 | quote = which estimates the number at between 500,000 and 1,000,000. 7 out of 10 Tutsis were killed}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Zungar2>{{cite book |last=Perdue |first=Peter C. |year=2005 |title=China Marches West: The Qing Conquest of Central Eurasia |publisher=Harvard University Press |isbn=978-0674016842 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J4L-_cjmSqoC }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Millward2007>{{cite book|last=Millward|first=James A.|title=Eurasian Crossroads: A History of Xinjiang|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8FVsWq31MtMC&pg=PA95|accessdate=August 13, 2016|year=2007|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-0-231-13924-3|page=95}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Sino1>{{cite 