abc.net.au/news/2014-05-02/rod-marsh-named-cas-chairman-of-selectors/5425812|title=Rod Marsh replaces John Inverarity as Australian cricket's chairman of selectors|work=ABC|date=2 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe current four-person panel for the Australia women's sides is: [[Shawn Flegler]] (chairman), [[Matthew Mott]] (head coach), [[Avril Fahey]] and [[Julie Hayes]].\n\n===Board of directors===\nCricket Australia is governed by eight (normally nine) independent directors, who work collectively in the national interest of Australian cricket.\n\nThe chief executive officer reports to the board of nine directors. The current eight board members are:\n* Earl Eddings (chairman)\n* Paul Green\n* John Harnden AM\n* Dr Lachlan Henderson\n* Jacquie Hey\n* [[Michael Kasprowicz]]\n* Michelle Tredenick\n* Richard Freudenstein\nLast update: 28 November 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cricketaustralia.com.au/about/our-board|title=Our Board |work=Cricket Australia|date=28 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Australia|Cricket}}\n* [[Australian national cricket team]]\n* [[Australia national women's cricket team]]\n* [[Cricket in Australia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* ''Wisden Cricketers Almanack''\n* {{cite book |last=Pollard |first=Jack |authorlink=Jack Pollard |title=Australian Cricket: The game and the players |year=1988 |publisher=Angus & Robertson |location=Sydney |isbn=0-207-15269-1}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.cricket.com.au/ Cricket Australia official website]\n* [http://www.facebook.com/CricketAustralia Official CA Facebook page]\n* [http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/index/0,22045,5006069,00.html Cricket Feature \u2013 Daily Telegraph]\n\n{{Australia national cricket team}}\n{{Cricket in Australia}}\n{{Full Members of the International Cricket Council}}\n{{Sports governing bodies in Australia}}\n\n[[Category:Cricket governing bodies in Australia|*]]\n[[Category:Cricket administration|Australia]]\n[[Category:Cricket adminis